name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Amazing place to walk especially during evening time, not so hot.
The breeze and sea sounds will calm your mind and soul.

Really like the idea to have cycling and walking/running path, no need to worry speeding bicycle.

Try to chit chat with people nicely, you might get some surprise:
Guy share his fishing tactic and one gentleman even let me walk his big dog.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Awesome place to visit for some nature and peace.  Greatly maintain trails - separate trails for jogging/biking and walking.  Clean beach and water but plenty of ships parked in a distance.

Lots of trees around, bbq pits, etc.  There are food/drink stalls and bike rentals.  As well as, children playground areas.  Seen people wind surfing, swimming, sailing, enjoying beach volleyball, fishing, etc.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Great for just about most outdoor activities- running, walking or just chilling in the splendor of the park. The park is well landscaped and a good atmosphere.

Whilst swimming is allowed,  it's not always opportune with the vast amount of shipping going by and whilst it is well maintained,  there is occasional debris and waste.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Weekday afternoons are the best time to visit to beat the crowd. More peaceful when there's lesser folks running/cycling around. Great for long walks, cycling, jogging. Sink in and forget all the worries of the world.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Incredibly beautiful!
If you're planning to spend a good time with your friends, family or partner in the evening then this is the right place for you to come. Make sure that you spend at least 3-4 hours and check out amazing points.
A view of the beach will make you fall in love. Also, you can get bicycles on rent and there is a separate track for the same.
There are a lot of other activities available for kids.
You can also bring your own food and eat there.
There is no entry fee as such in order to enter into the park/beach.
Check out some pictures that I have clicked.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Nice place to get close to the sea, not a great beach for swimming as lots of ships and the water is not clear. Had some good fun. Good for family with small kids, also perfect for cycling, practice skating and have some fresh air.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Great place to spend time with your friends, and loved ones. Whatever activities that you like to do outdoor, East Coast Park is the place. With a long sandy beach from Gardens by the Bay all the way to Changi beach where you can swim, jog, cycle or simply walk by the beach. Perfect during sunny day or when it's windy.

It's best not to do any activity when it looks like it's about to rain. Cause it can be down pour without warning and you will not be able to find any shelter nearby where you are at that moment. As there are not too many shelters along the coast.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
One of my favourite places to hang out, cycling, jogging, walking or to have a barbecue by the beach.

Since I got to Sg , I'm going there every month and it's always a good vibe, the view and just a fresh air.

You can book a barbecue pit or rent a bicycle,Boat , etc.

It's quite a few  of bars and restaurants around the area as well.

If you like to exercise that will be a good spot to run or play some volleyball.

Cheers

name: East Coast Park
review_text: A place to go for casual landscape photography. You get a happy lonely feelings which is what I want in this place. At the same time there are  restaurants ready to fill your hunger. Do not miss renting a bicycle to ride safely along paths parallel to the coastline. I had a wonderful time. If you have freedom of time than go during one of the weekdays.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: What a lovely public amenity to have next to the water, so many people enjoying the outdoors and cycling or jogging, or walking or stopping for snacks, or sitting under the trees and watching the world go by. Quite lovely. Lots of parking available.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: I'd say that walking by the beach and riding a bike at the East Coast Park are two of my best experiences while on tour in Singapore. My senior companions decided to just sleep it off/ watch movie at the hotel during our last day in Singapore but I don't want to waste the chance to explore places so I made my own plans. Though it's raining that morning, I decided to walk from the hotel to this seaside park. It was such a joyful experience to be so close to nature! After walking by the beach, I decided to rent a bike which was cool because all you have to do is scan a QR code to do so.  It took me a while to figure it out but, luckily, I was able to unlock the bike and finally use it. This was the first time I biked in a foreign country (and all by myself) so this small adventure is quite memorable for me. Small joys!

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
This being just about the only beach that is large enough for swimming, tanning, picnics, bbq and other activities, it has been transformed by the government over the years into a place to hangout and have some fun. The water is now cleaner than ever, and is actually quite clear, compared to the murky, oily sludge of old.
Here, you can rent bicycles, take a nice stroll along the shore, fish at the jetty, and even go wake boarding. Hungry? Restaurants, cafes and a hawker centre offer a variety of food.
As always, weekdays are quieter, and recommended if you want to go.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great Place to have chill out especially for glamping parties and volley ball games at the beach with family. East Coast Park is a must to go place on a regular basis to have some get away from all the electronic gadgets. "Make the days memorable with intentional efforts".

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
The pictures and views say everything of this amazing place. Good place for cycling and hangout with families during weekends.

There’re bicycle rental around as well. Or else, if you plan to ride, you can get Anywheel or bicycle rental around the park as well.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: It's the best part of East. Best suited for  picnics, cycling, jogging, and enjoying beach side view. The food courts are spread across  and have plenty of options. It's a very well planned park.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Singapore's longest stretch of park/beach. One of the best place to relax and have fun. Plenty of different F&B outlets spread across the park. There are also a number of bicycle rental shops where you can rent bicycles. If you want an easy and fuss free stretch of cycling path to cycle, you can't go wrong in cycling at East Coast Park. However do be aware that certain part may be crowded during peak timings, but if you want to avoid crowds for your picnic, then  avoid the middle portion where the McDonald's is and where the hawker centre is.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Very, very crowded on the weekends. If you want to rent a bike during then, you’ll have to queue for pretty long. And too much traffic. Go on a weekday and it’s a much better experience. Nice photo spots as well. Don’t miss Bedok Jetty!

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
I had an amazing and relaxing time at this place! There were tons of fun activities to spend your free time, and the park stretched almost two kilometers along the east coast. The park had a well-equipped children's playground, a skating platform, and many other amenities. The beach was clean and shallow, making it the ideal spot for a Sunday outing.

Additionally, there was a jetty built alongside the beach, providing a breathtaking view of the sea and planes traversing through Changi Airport. I even heard that they have camping sites available, which seems to be popular among the locals.

Overall, I would highly recommend this place for anyone looking for a fun and relaxing day out. Whether you're with family, friends, or on your own, there's something for everyone at this park!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Fabulous visit. Started with a paddle board lesson at Aloha Sea Sports followed by a walk with the family. Lots of space for walkers and cyclists. Had lunch at High Tide Bar & Bistro which I highly recommend.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Loved it. Beautiful place. Nice camping areas and bbq pits. Quite enjoyed the overall idea of having this beautiful park that'd act as a great barrier in events of flooding. But I love the amenities and enjoyed my walk there.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Catch the lovely sunset at East Coast Park. Its been a tired week, brought family out for bonding and relax. Listen to the sound of the sea waves, enjoy the lovely sunset scenery. The view is awesome. Its a nice place to relax with your family. With a big opening field behind to play ball games, sandy beach at the front. And we happened to saw a group of parrot lovers flying their birds around the area. It's a real bonus to us.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Excellent food, well plated and well served
Sometimes a little difficult to get the servers attention, but in all fairness it was packed
Once you had their attention, service was quick and good

Will definitely visit again and again

Btw, loved the non-meat options. Maybe they could consider expanding that part of the menu

Loved the free refills too

All in all, a very nice Brunch

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Love the accessibility to this place, all the way from MBS. Many spots to take breaks at for refreshing yourself. Campsites available. BBQ spots. And much more! Once a week must visit for cycling enthusiasts or as a hangout spot.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: My boys love to come here for camping. Very relaxing place. Even come during the hot sunny day the wind still blow very strong. Kids can play sand while adult can sit there and enjoy the sea breeze.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Excellent place for long walks, relaxing and peaceful, have all amenities - food, drink, washroom. The park that you can go anytime. I did a solo Yoga session on one of the evenings near the beach (free of charge) and felt great as people jog and skate further away. Hardly get distracted but air and wind was good. Some folks were just enjoying the breeze on chairs.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: A very peaceful and serene environment for people to exercise or chill. There are bicycle renting facilities, public toilets with shower facilities and some F&B eateries located in different parts across the stretch eg Coffee Bean & Tea Leaves, Old Town Coffee and Macdonald's to name a few.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: This place is one of the best places for you to enjoy the different vibe of Singapore. It's a good place for jogging and cycling after your busy day, a healing place and a good spot for catching sunset.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Easy Coast Park is a nice place to go cycling. It's a long stretch with lots of shade from the trees.

There are toilets and vending machines scattered across the length of the park.

There's also many food options to choose from when looking for a place to grab a bite.

Overall its a nice place to go for a relaxing walk or ride.

The only downside is that it's not that easy to access by public transport

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
In terms of brightness, East Coast Park is definitely much brighter than Changi Beach Park so for evening walk, I prefer East Coast Park :-)

Many people like to camp or bbq here so you will see many tents along the park/beach.

Can eat at nearby makan places (a lot) then take a long walk to help digestion :-)

name: East Coast Park
review_text: A great place to visit, to have a stroll, jog and cycle by the beach. Enjoy the breeze and sunshine. Enjoy the view of the sea.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Best place to relax , surrounded by beach and greenery.... The cool breeze in the evening is awesome... U may come for the cycling also, and have ur evening walk... U may come with your friends to chill and drink or snacking..

It has the best sunset view

It's behind the parkway parade mall and Grand mercure Roxy hotel.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: The sand are dirty and the waters are not clean . Look at all the ships parked at the water and you will understand why. For economic survival the ships are essential to singapore even though they cause pollution to our sea water .

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
It's a pretty place but please go during non-peak/non-festive timings.

Went on the night of 23rd October - lots of drunkards and overflowing trash cans, rubbish everywhere, some clogged toilets and vomit in the washroom sinks. Not the fault of the people managing the area, it's just the people visiting.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Public commute with walking isn't so bad ah, just have to go through a shady tunnel. Booked a BBQ pit by the shore and it was AMAZING other than the huge crane doing construction behind the area. Also, I advise checking the weather before going bc I was positively drenched in rain, and the BBQ didn't start until 7pm (we are newbies to BBQ). Loved the whole experience, though! I should've asked my relatives for tips first sia...

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
As one can expect, this strip of coast is very crowded, especially over the weekend. It is nice that the cycle and walking lanes are seperate so makes less chance of collision.. some evenings you can see the beautiful kites flying.. good sea breeze although sometimes smells like petrol.. I guess you will get that with a 100 cargo ships out in front. Beautiful spot for the sunset. I do enjoy coming down here for a walk when I can. There are also exercise stations to work out on.
I have not swam yet but having done some research, apparently it is graded as "good" and meets WHO standards.. there are maps on the paths at night time.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: I really love ECP. It's quiet, chilled, everyone seems happy, and there's just a brilliant and chilled vibe about the place, come rain or shine. There are also some amazing cafes and restaurants along the front too including Central Thai (sit and watch the world go by), Basil & Thyme (amazing Thai with epic service - try the beef noodles!) and St Marks (great burgers).

name: East Coast Park
review_text: A Wonderful afternoon perfect for Cycling after rain. Love the weather so much and packed up with kids to cycle all the way from East Coast park to MBS for dinner. The route is pleasant, away from the normal weekends crowds! Love it!!!! Great exercise and definitely great way to listen to music and enjoying the scenery along the way!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Experience night cycling from changi point to Marina south pier is the best and nice with new paths open,cool and windy feel fresh whether, weekend crowded with people cycling, fishing and overnight camping.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Great park to plan a cycle 🚴‍♂️ trip that will take you to Gardens by the Bay, Marina Barrage, Marina Bay, to Merlion, Singapore F1 track etc. ~ Return trip duration ranges from 1 hour to 4 hours back to ECP.

Went for a stroll this Tuesday morning & afternoon. It was free & easy. Not crowded. Road is well-shaded by big trees 🌳
• comfortable for walking 🚶🏻
• pet 🦮 friendly areas
• cycling track assigned🪧
• safe walking path 🚶🏻‍♀️🚸,
• beachfront views and forest views. 🏝 Nice palm trees.
• Well-maintained park.

I love cycling at East Coast Park. Walking is fairly enjoyable as well.

Accessible by bus. Walking duration is quite long, can use underpass.

Pro tip: Plan your transportation to stop near your desired arrival point inside ECP. E.g Bike rental B, PS Cafe or Coastal Playgrove, etc.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Nice and cosy park for a walk, relax or enjoy family time.
However, will still hear all the noises from vehicles due to near to the main road as the only down side.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
One of the best parks in Singapore (or maybe the best). The park with the longest stretch? Best for cycling, chilling, picnic, kite flying, and family time. You can watch airplanes on their descend before they land in Changi.

There are many entries into this park and it connects you to Changi Airport and the City — Marina Barrage to Gardens By the Bay then Merlion. Has lots of restaurants and places to eat. If you don’t have a bike, scooter, or skateboard, there are bike rentals and bikes for group/family where you can take your family/kids or your bae.

There are also places to do water sports/activities — in the Water Ski Park or at the sea. Also lots of very nice playgrounds for kids and adults (swings). And don’t forget to visit the Bedok Jetty and have a relaxing walk during a cloudy day or at midnight.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
the skate park is closed, and some parts of the park is under construction. bus 401 is also suspended because of reduced demand due to covid. just some points to take note of yeah.

——————

anyway, this park is bootiful. you could rent a bike from the gocycling rental place at area c3 and chill around the park. family bikes are cool too. the stretch of coastline is very narrow, but very long, stretching all the way from marina east to changi jurassic mile. the sea view is a bit discouraging but at least you can see 69 trillion ships waiting in the water to go to tanjong pagar. anyway a cool day for me

(btw come on weekdays less crowd even in the hols and there are offers for the bikes as well: buy 1h for 2h while weekend its buy 2h for 3h)

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Very clean and nice peaceful place to visit.. Specially if you want to to be with family  or just want to chill having bbq picnic it's the perfect place ..You can also rent a bicycle and cycle around..

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Love the beach. Good for running, relaxing and picnic. 🌊🐚 Sound of the waves and wind is 😍❤️

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Best place in Singapore to have a good family outing. Many nice places to sit along the beach and many activities to do in the area.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Enjoy while it lasts, as they are going to build a new island (reclaimed land) just right on this park. The park is nice with paved road along the coast. There are countless of ship on the horizon and the air is so polluted from these ship.

The beach is not swimmable either.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Carpark C4 has bicycle rentals, our church went for baptism today in the sea, such a glorious event though it was raining. Had so much fun and laughter!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great for relax place, walk and cycling. Little bit crowded but very lively.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Good place to unwind and relax and catch some sea breeze. Best to go during weekdays, as it gets pretty crowded on weekends.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
breathtaking view in morning and evening sunshine and sunset are main focus to visit.
Clean beaches with lots of stuff nearby

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Cycling and walking is fun on weekdays, not much crowd and the coast is clean. The wind is cooling under the hot rays of sunshine 😄

name: East Coast Park
review_text: East Cost Park - one of Singapore’s most treasured urban getaways, offering a wide range of recreational, sporting and dining activities for all walk of life. Definitely a top choice for family bonding outdoor activities over the weekends.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: A place to be. U can do walking jogging cycling skating etc along with picnic yoga camping & dining. Cycling available on rental and washrooms there at every refresh station.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Very nice cyclist park for kid to cycle around..certain area of the park cyclist just zoom here and there so beware if you are a novice. They should allow some street seller like ice cream or snack seller so that it will be more fun over there.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Nice park to walk around... of course with the great view of the cargo ships 😂 since we are one of the busiest ports in the world...
Nice cafe along the park to rest and relax and read a book

name: East Coast Park
review_text: It is a wonderful place to visit. A truly mesmerizing sunset. Excellent cleanliness and neatness. Proper management of BBQ pits. A place to sit with family and friends. At night it looks fabulous in case you want to sit alone.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Came here for a bike ride with friends. The original plan was to cycle back and forth from here to MBS. But suddenly there was a thunderstorm and we couldn’t get there😭 it was interesting to see so many planes landing. Want to come here again. Love this place!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Had a late night walk with friends after dinner at the nearby restaurant. The park was bright and feel safe. Lot of families and friends were seen hanging out and chill. There's separate running/walking path from bicycle. But still need to be careful for those with small kids since the cyclist were a bit too speedy.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Very beautiful park along the east coast of Singapore. You can rent a bike or skates here and explore.
There are facilities for camping as well.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: So beautiful sunset.. Nice place for gathering to bbq and walking distance from carpark. Windy and relaxing

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Love the number of public toilets...the space for everywalks of life in this park and ideal for watching sun rise and catching saline breeze...excellent for your lungs

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Always lovely to have a stroll. Weekends tend to be rather overcrowded though. Stunning sky and horizon sea views.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: East coast was a beautiful place for relaxation,it has a wide parking,food village , playground for kids and wide space for recreational.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
The place is comfortable for a vacation with family, because there are many facilities here, the place is quite comfortable even though it is seafront.
Tracks for running and cycling are available, bicycle rental is also available

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
21 Feb 2023: East Coast… East Coast Park experienced flooding due to Spring tides.

07 Sep 2022: Scenic coastal views…be it listening to the sound of the crashing sea waves, BBQ or camping with permit at designated areas or going for a run, cycle, skating or other forms of exercises; East Coast Park is a great place for outing or get close to the sea.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: If you plan to cycle from city hall to east coast, estimated time around 3 hrs. It's wonderful time to exercise over there. I like the food at the hawker, other than that,  the Thai restaurant is awesome too.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
No introduction needed for Singapore’s most popular recreational track, be it cycling 🚴‍♂️, walking🚶‍♂️or running 🏃‍♀️, along 15-km of beach, the longest in Singapore.

Opened in 1972, the 460-acre East Coast Park is built entirely on reclaimed land with man-made beaches where swimming protected by breakwaters.

There are multiple activities catering to all interests although strangely, swimming is not advisable.🐵

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Its your the DESTINATION for a break from you hectic schedule ans chill out with friends and have some family time
Many restraunts and coffee shop like coffee Beans and Starbucks also , Biryani House, Mc Donalds Patros and etc

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Artificial as it may be, it's a really nice place to jog and relax with friends and family

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Nice place to visit and hangout with family and friends! Beautiful sunset view with majestic blue sky and relaxing sound of waves

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Fantastic location by the sea, perfect for cycling, jogging, family outing, fishing,  and relaxing. Great place for nature lovers. I would recommend it as a must visit place in Singapore.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: A nice coast to take a stroll in the evening, to get a taste of sea air and relax. And probably the best part is tasty barbecue with fresh coconut juice or a beer.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
A nice place to have outing activities with family or friends. Clean place and foods around to eat after cycling or volleyballs games or even catch up for chats.

Today was super crowded when we went, it was great to see everyone having activities outdoor but sad to say there was no social distance around and it is bad.

Was there for a while and then we head off to avoid the crowds together.

IG @mommyserene

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Nice place to chill out and clear the mind. Sometimes someone needs a place to just zone out and be left alone . Visited in the early hours of the morning. Although the sea was dark, I could see the slightly lighted sky in a far distance was a beautiful sight. The place is lighted well. When I was there a few of the eateries were open even at wee hours of the early mornings. You have your coffee and Beans, Mac Donalds and an Indian Muslim restaurant. But I was there for some peace and time. Such a nice place to be alone.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
One of the oldest park in Singapore linking the city to East Coast of Singapore.
A must visit to all visitors in Singapore.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great place for kids. Huge park with many play areas. So realxing.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
The East Coast Parkway (or ECP for us locals) stretches from Marina Barrage all the way to Changi - where it turns into the "Changi Treadmill" or the "Changi Grinder" depending on your level of depravity.

The ECP is for everyone! There's tonnes of activities to do along the way, you'll see Filipino groups having BBQs, sing songs, and just a jolly good time. During Xmas they turn the dial to 11 and punch out Feliz Navidad till it is stuck in your head for a month.

You can rent bikes, camp in tents, go sailing, picnic and BBQ, exercise (you'll see runners, walkers, rollerbladers, cyclists, quad bikers, tandem cyclists)... you name it everyone is doing it.

During Covid-19 / The Coov / The Pandemic / Whatevs you wanna call it, this park is a sanctuary for your mental health, get here as often as you can and get your life in balance. Enjoy my friends!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Nice park. Good to eat brunch or ride a bike. But the beach isn't clean and the view is on the container ship.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: It is what you'd expect from a park beside the beach - nice breeze, beach activities and a good flow of people. Food and toilets were spread out nicely. One section of lights was turned off at night, causing a stretch to be quite dark.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Great cycling day! Except it rained heavily on the way back.
MBS - Jewel - MBS

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great place for relaxing if you want to visit the beach in Singapore. There is a food court near the beach.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Very windy at night and great park for a walk or relax after a hards day work. You will feel calm with the nature breeze. Various car park lots available and public restrooms. Great for running too.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Nice view and ambiance and the waves of the sea are beautiful to behold

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Siglap Canal, near Carpark and toilet at D1.
Stop and admire the beautiful flowers along the road divider along ECP, towards East Coast Seafood Centre from Marina Cove direction.

Thank you Nparks for the greening efforts and making Singapore a 'City in Nature'.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Just stunning! Rent a bike and cycle for miles with stunning views!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Parked @ East Coast Carpark F3 & cycled to Changi Airport Terminal 2, great relaxing ride and totally interesting.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
My bike had punctured tire and I was far away from bike. Luckily my friend manage to catch up on this GoCycling
Shop which is about to close. the guy was so helpful to just wait for me before he leaves as the shop is already close. really a saviour of the night

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great place for a casual day of fun with cycling, jogging, playing in the beach and visiting a multitude of different f&b choices. Beach is not the best with a view of many tanker ships and boats. However sand is decent and you can have a good time in this beach!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Dedicated cycling routes along the park make my commuting rides very enjoyable during weekdays early morning and evening. Well, I heard weekends are pretty crowded. Of course, I've seen on my commutes even Friday evening can be relatively more crowded than other weekdays evening. As of Jan 2023, the whole park is fully accessible apart from construction areas. During new year day and the holiday day after it, I have seen certain areas were extremely packed with campers.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Such a lovely stretch of the park. So well maintained.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Beautiful and very green place, lots of places for walking or jogging, fresh sea breeze by your side....relax with Nature

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Feel blessed that I can ride a bike for 10 minutes to reach this park. Try to avoid weekends. Clean and well maintained. Park goers tend to adhere to the rules but watch out for the small children as sometimes they will wander into your path.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: East coast Park is an excellent place when you want to spend a casual out door time with your family. You can enjoy the sunshine, see walking dogs and hear the tides there. Also the slides playground is great for your energetic children (it is free!).

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Big carpark and free parking at D4&D5. Good nature, view, and get fresh air.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great cycling trail with a long stretch of nice sea view. Bicycle rentals available at affordable hourly rate. Quite crowded with groups of cyclists and families even during weekdays.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Great place to enjoy the beach, cleaner than other beaches and there's benches to sit as well

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Great place to spend time with friends and family alike. Plenty of sheltered seats for breaks or in the event of rain. There are F&B options along the way as well. They accept cashless payment options as well so it’s perfectly okay to turn up in just your sports attire and have your phone/smartwatch.

If you are renting bicycles, just remember to check the brakes, chains and also gears to ensure a smooth and safe ride.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Cycling to ecp from home and onto MBS/city. It is a nice way to cycle. Sometimes it gets busy but usually it’s nice. Give it a go! And seafood at east coast is also legit

name: East Coast Park
review_text: It's fun to get together and grilled foodstuffs.. off day chill time..

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
One of the last remaining old school parks with an actual beach. Much has improved over the years, hawker still there but much more dining options than before. Bicycle rentals are still available but check where to park your car.
Also one of those ironic places where you can either bring your date or when you got dumped.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Nice place and the beach clean for play water , like it .. can rilex and enjoying the win

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
If you're in Singapore for a few days, then you need to take a stroll/ride/walk at East Coast Park. It's a 10km stretch of well organised and paved walk and cycle way.
Ideally go on weekdays mornings and not the weekend as it tends to be very crowded.
You can walk all the way to Chanji Village if you have the stamina and endurance for it!
Mozzie repelant is a must for most people!

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Amazing place for relax and exercise nice beach  ships viewing on here

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Just a nice place to cycle and relax.  There's a bicycle kiosk near the food centre. Rent a bike from there if you go there for food and enjoy the scenery.

name: East Coast Park

name: East Coast Park

East Coast Park is such an amazing place for leisure cycling, walking, picnic, listening to sea breeze, water sport, kite flying, star gazing, roller blading, dog run and great seafood.

The scenery is captivating, gorgeous and vibrant during sunrise and sunset.

Watching on the sand and listening to the sea waves are therapeutic to the soul.

It's a place where you can take great photos for nature lovers.

There's bbq pit where you can also hold parties at.

The toilets are clean and newly refurbished.

There are also bicycle kiosks around as well as SG bikes for rental.

#ILoveEastCoastPark

review_text:
Beautiful ambience.
This beach has the Bluish sea water and no sharp stones (not dirty or muddy like Pasir Ris or Changi beach)

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Just spent a lovely day at East Coast Park. So much to see and do. You can’t visit without trying out the Hawkers food. There are undercover tables and chairs all over the place. There weren’t a lot open at lunchtime, but the food we found and has freshly cooked was scrummy. Great value too. First things first, we ordered a bucket full of ice and bottles of beer and then, one by one (there were four of us) we would each go to a food stall and come back with a plate of heaven ... there are different cuisines, Malaysian, Cantonese, Singaporean .. pork, steak, noodles, seafood ... you name it, they had it. Take a walk along the beach or grassed areas or hire a bike. Our children enjoyed wake boarding while the adults chilled with a drink at a bar. The view from the beach was a bit industrial with countless tankers and container ships moored offshore but the water looked nice and relaxing. There was a tow skiing place just down the beach and a bit of a fun park with restaurants and other amenities. The only challenge to the day was getting a taxi back to the hotel. Hardly any around in the day. Great day though.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: An amazing park to visit. It is suitable for all ages. It is linked to many places like Gardens by the Bay. There are many bicycle rentals that you could use to enjoy cycling around the park. The staff are knowledgeable and very friendly, so you can approach them if your bicycle is faulty or the tyres do not have enough air. There is, of course, the beach where you can do a variety of things such as swimming in the ocean, sunbathing, picnicking etc. Also, you can see the vast ocean that extends to Batam, as well as industrial boats moving. Sometimes, you can even see police boats patrolling the ocean. There is also a nearby food court where you can purchase food to replenish your strength if you’re exercising. You can invite your friends and loved ones to come to this park. Having visited East Coast Park, you will have mesmerising memories of your enjoyable experiences there. I really recommend visiting this park if you haven't yet.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: The place is very windy and spacious; not only width, but length as well! The beach and walkway speads over miles on the east side and it would take a lot of energy to cover it. There are tracks for man-powered vehicles and a track for walking. The soft, cool breeze just improves the experience. Also, the beaches are beautiful too! Don't hesitate to dip your feet in the cool water; but do not swim as it is a rule. You can enjoy camping overnight as well! Overall, it is a great place to enjoy your "me" time!

name: East Coast Park

great place to camp with family or friends,

Campsite G is very quiet and calm nice place to relax, good toilet, less spot to swim and the sudden  waves can be quite dangerous for kids, far from foodcourt, and might need to rent bike to go there.

name: East Coast Park

review_text: Used to live in Marine Terrace since I was born. And even though I've moved to Jurong and to Bedok after got married, I still visit this place often. The best place to do your picnics, barbecues and go for a walk too.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
East Coast Park is one of Singapore's most treasured urban getaways, offering an invigorating and exciting diversity of sporting, dining and recreational . If there’s one place in Singapore that’s synonymous with sporty outdoor activities, it’s East Coast Park, where some seven million locals and tourists flock to for the variety of sporting, entertainment and dining attractions.
Along this 15-kilometre stretch of beach, you’ll find hordes of cyclists and roller bladers enjoying the sun and sea breeze, while cable skiing and water sports are on offer for those who prefer offshore and aquatic activities.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: After years of coming to East Coast Park, it is still one of my favourite spot to hang out by the beach. Despite close to noon where the sun is shining high up and blazing hot, there are enough trees to hide from the sun. There are even lots of seats and chair to sit and chill together with the sound of waves washing ashore coupe with strong coolding winds that blows into your skin despite the hot sun. Do try the bicycle if you want to explore the whole park.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: The weather is always pleasant with a cool breeze. Great for walking, jogging, cycling and skating. There is facility for hiring cycles and skates by the hour. There is wave park for line skiing, and water sport facilities (Stand-up paddling and wind surfing). There are separate areas for camping and BBQ pits available for booking as well. Absolute bliss of a place.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Paradise for runners and walkers. Lot of other activities such as cycling, skating, fishing etc are also available. There are separate tracks for running and cycling. There is also a skating park. Shops for taking cycles on rent are also there. You can enjoy beach and Bedok jetty which is a place for fishing. Sea food is also available. There are many maintained washrooms inside the park.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Road near the popular areas are nice and mostly smooth. once it gets further out towards Changi the road gets pretty uneven and not in the best standards. However, most people don't go all the way there so it's not too bad. Lighting can get quite dark towards the end but is relatively lit at popular areas. Cycling shops available to rent bicycles at a few spots and sea breeze is quite nice though sand can be a little dirty. Overall a nice place to go.

name: East Coast Park

name: East Coast Park
review_text: East Coast Park in Singapore is a beautiful beach with bike trail, cool restaurants, outdoor sports areas & camping spots right by the water. Perfect getaway place! Love this place 😍

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
An excellent place overall. Great for jogging and you may have a chance to catch the sunrise/sunset if there is little cloud cover.

There's great food and a big playground at Marine Cove. A great recreational space for families, cyclists and everyone else.

However, it is a bit difficult to access East Coast Park by public bus as there is only 1 bus (Bus 401) that passes through it.

Very peaceful and quiet during weekdays but tends to be noisy and crowded during weekends and public holidays especially during the Chinese New Year and National Day holidays (every 9 Aug)

name: East Coast Park

name: East Coast Park
review_text: Loved ECP all my life. Cycling, sitting and watching the waves go by, long walks, fishing at the jetty or just watching the planes take off and land. What more can one ask for :)

The beautiful beach side alongside the running track just adds to the experience and you can see the dawn break in and the city get all lit up as it turns 6am (ish)!

name: East Coast Park

review_text: Was an excited day during the last visit as Singapore held the Sail GP for the first time in Asia. Great performance by all the Catamaran Sailors. My first live Sail events which also near my house.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
East Coast Park is a beach and a park encompassing Marine Parade, Bedok and Tampines, along the southeastern coast of Singapore. It was opened in the 1970s, when the government had completed reclaiming land off the coast at Katong which extends from Changi to Kallang. It serves various seaside communities such as Kallang, Marine Parade and Bedok.

Good place to spend time,
One can do camping overnight by taking permission from the authorities.
parking is available,

The 185 hectare East Coast Park is the largest park in Singapore, and is built entirely on reclaimed land with a man-made beach, where swimming is possible. The beach is protected by breakwaters.

The park has barbecue pits, chalets, food centres and amenities for various sports activities. Visitors can fish at Bedok Jetty (Area F). A cycling and inline skating track runs along the perimeter of the park, which measures over 15 km long. It is connected to Changi Beach Park by the Coastal Park Connector Network, a 12 km park connector running along Tanah Merah Coast Road.

The National Sailing Centre, run by the Singapore Sailing Federation, conducts activities such as sailing and wind surfing.[55]

East Coast Lagoon Food Centre	Edit
The East Coast Lagoon Food Centre is a hawker centre near the East Coast Lagoon.
Occupying 0.81 ha (2.0 acres), the centre was constructed by the Public Works Department in 1977 at a cost of $700,000, with seating for 1,200 and 60 stalls. Constructed out of wood, the centre consisted of 10 structures, with butterfly-shaped roofs for the cooking areas and pyramid-shaped ones for the eating areas, and its design was intended to blend in with the seaside and the lagoon.

In 2003, as part of a redevelopment plan for the park, the hawker centre received an upgrade. In late 2013, the hawker centre was upgraded at a cost of $1.5 million. As part of the upgrade, the toilets were renovated and the seating capacity increased. Roofing and wooden floors were also installed.

Phase 1 of the precinct, with an area of about 9,800 sq m, is located to the west of Watson Road. It was previously a works area for the Central-Wan Chai Bypass (CWB) project.

People can reach the precinct from MTR Fortress Hill Station exit A by walking along Oil Street and Electric Road, and then going to the end of Watson Road, taking about seven minutes.

If you are here in the middle of the day and just want to grab a bite to eat, why not the newly refurbished macdonalds. Thanks to the efforts put in place by the national parks board in Singapore. The beach is kept clean and is very safe for families to come down and have fun. The only negative I will point out is that it may be rather hard to get to if you do not decide to head there by car or taxi. Be warned that weekends here are especially crowded with families and groups of students. If you are in Singapore and have nothing to do for a day. review_text:

There are a couple of bike hire places as well as a skate park, playgrounds and right up north there is a sailing place next to Stella's restaurant which is right under the flight path.   Definitely worth a walk up there and finish with lunch by the sea.
Anywhere on the ECP is a great place to watch the sunrise!  Enjoy all it has to offer.

review_text:
Nice park, might be one of the top parks. Good for dog walking, running and cycling.

But certain "popular" areas near bicycle rentals, hawker centre, McDonald's and cafes etc tend to be very crowded with pedestrians walking across the lanes without a care. Even parents with young children. It's dangerous for cyclists so make sure you go really slow around those areas. Speed up before and after those areas for a pleasant ride. Go all the way to Changi terminals or Changi beach park

review_text:
The park is a popular place for people to relax and unwind.The park has barbecue pits, chalets, food centers and amenities for various sports activities. Visitors can fish at Bedrock Jetty.A cycling and inline skating track runs along the perimeter of the park, which measures over 15 km long. It is connected to Changi Beach Park by the Coastal Park Connector Network, an 8 km park connector running along Changi Coast Road.

Overnight camping is permitted in East Coast Park

review_text: Sunny at times, cooling at nights. It brings one to the forlorn wonder of the crown of the southeastern tip of the Red Dot. On a normal sunny morning besieged by the burning humidity, we find joggers, couples, small groups of friends and tents that dot the sandy patches of grass by the waysides. To find inspiration for writing reviews, one only need to stay by the sandy benches, look aloof at the blue horizons and find meaning in life, gazing off far into the distance.

review_text:
In a country that is small and highly urbanized , a beach is a welcomed antidote to the hectic lifestyle.

Open spaces , seaside , nice white sand and a relaxed atmosphere .

Swim , play with sea water , kick around the sand , cycling , feel the wind , watch people jogging , look at the ship's and boats berthed on the sea , etc . All rest and relaxation activities. And these are free of charge .

U can barbecue there too . Though u have to book the pits in advance.( U pay )

I am not telling u about the eating places there , for there are many , in different varieties and styles . You know what to do and what to eat if u have cravings.

Though the beach is not really formed naturally , I am  happy to have it there .

Take a break there , you deserve it.

review_text:
Our very own East Coast with a Plan they say 😜

An awesome 7km stretch beach/shoreline with various amenities and facilities.

One needs to spend at least a day to explore the entire stretch. From seafood lovers to skateparks to beautiful sunsets, there's always something for everyone here.

Family friendly activities like kayaking, cycling and roller blading are a hit during the weekends so do cone early!

Parking space is aplenty at different sections across the park/beach. But will be usually filled to the brim on weekends/peak periods. Patience is a virtue for this part.

review_text: I like this place a lot. It was a really good place to enjoy a holiday or free time alone or with friends and family. The beach was clean with blue sky. I came all the way down from Burgis to East coast park for sunset but instead of seeing sunset, I saw the light from heaven and it was gorgeous. Many people were there for outdoor activities such as going picnic, playing soccer, going fishing, etc. It was so close to the airport so that I could see airplanes flying around and sometimes I could see the logo of the airlines really clear. It was interesting. Although it was close to the airport, we couldn't hear any sound from the airplane. Outside, we could see many huge ships which carrying goods but there was no trace of oil on water and that was amazing. If you are in SG, you should visit East coast park

The PCN is good for cycling too and there are bikes renting service as well. Of course there are beers too.
Have a nice relax here.

review_text:
It's a good link to the eastern sectors of the country, especially the CBD. Mini park connectors stem out from ECP via underpasses to move around SG by bicycle for example.

Nice and windy with a relatively pleasant atmosphere. Good seaside restaurants and a few local style hawkers,

Nonetheless, as far as beaches go, don't expect anything such as waves and fun coast side swimming. The water here is still and boring. Go for a cycle ride.

It's Interesting to see that some people have started Kiteboarding.

Main drawback is its accessibility via public transportation. Also a lack of affordable food choices (cheapest is probably Mcdonalds at marina cove / small hawker centre)

The toilet facilities were also kept relatively clean and pleasant with a few fancy restaurants around which we didn't visit.

But definitely a place to visit for families and people who enjoy the outdoors and nature.

name: East Coast Park
review_text: East Coast Park certainly brings back the fond memories of having picnic with the family, road safety park organized by the primary school and the coolest McDonald's to be hanging out during my teenage years. One thing missing was the "Viking" ride near to where the McDonald's was. Now, facilities has been added/upgraded and the cycling path(PCN) has more reach than it ever did before; what's not to love? IMHO, having modern amenities with a touch of nostalgia, evokes a vibe that I simply could not resist.

name: East Coast Park
review_text:
Park's geography renders it an excellent choice for exercise without having to double back on yourself. Lots to see and do, drink and eat, with a large number of clean facilities all the way up to the bottom of Changi airport.

Be mindful of walking/jogging in the cycle path, and for cyclists out exercising (rather than sauntering) try and stick to the service road going east, else there's a mismatch of speed/expectation which would be a recipe for disaster.

Something for everyone, just make sure you take your litter home - it's hard to see the extent of the cleanup operation on a Monday morning.
